title: King Kong
description: A film crew goes to a tropical island for an exotic location shoot and discovers a colossal ape who takes a shine to their female blonde star.

title: Duck Soup
description: Rufus T. Firefly is named president/dictator of bankrupt Freedonia and declares war on neighboring Sylvania over the love of his wealthy backer Mrs. Teasdale.

title: The Invisible Man
description: A scientist finds a way of becoming invisible, but in doing so, he becomes murderously insane.

title: 42nd Street
description: When the leading lady of a Broadway musical twists her ankle, a young chorus girl is given her big chance to be a star.

title: Gold Diggers of 1933
description: Four aspiring actresses struggle to make ends meet during the Depression and try to find wealthy husbands while rehearsing for a Broadway show.

title: Queen Christina
description: Queen Christina of Sweden is a popular monarch who is loyal to her country, but falls in love with a Spanish envoy and must choose between her throne and the man she loves.

title: Footlight Parade
description: A musical producer tries to outdo his rivals by creating elaborate, live prologues for movie theaters, leading to a frantic rush to stage three massive numbers.

title: Little Women
description: The four March sisters grow up in Civil War era New England, dealing with poverty, illness, family, and love.

title: The Private Life of Henry VIII
description: King Henry VIII of England discards one wife after another in his pursuit of an heir and a love that lasts.

title: Design for Living
description: A woman cannot decide between two men who love her, so the three of them agree to try living together in a platonic friendly relationship.

title: I'm No Angel
description: A circus performer seeks a better life and finds it with a wealthy man, but his friends and family try to break them up.

title: She Done Him Wrong
description: A seductive nightclub singer contends with several suitors, including a jealous escaped convict and a handsome young temperance league member.

title: Dinner at Eight
description: A high-society dinner party in New York City highlights the financial and personal woes of its aristocratic guests and their servants.

title: The Testament of Dr. Mabuse
description: A police inspector investigates a series of crimes that seem to be orchestrated by Dr. Mabuse, a criminal mastermind who is supposedly locked away in an asylum.

title: Zero for Conduct
description: In a repressive French boarding school, four boys plot a rebellion against their strict teachers and the administration.

title: Sons of the Desert
description: Stan and Ollie trick their wives into thinking Ollie is sick so they can sneak away to a convention in Chicago.

title: Cavalcade
description: A portrayal of English life from New Year's Eve 1899 to New Year's Day 1933 through the eyes of well-to-do Londoners.

title: Morning Glory
description: A naive small-town girl comes to New York City determined to become a successful stage actress.

title: Flying Down to Rio
description: A band leader pursues a beautiful woman to Rio de Janeiro, but complications arise when she is already engaged. Notable for the first screen pairing of Fred Astaire and Ginger Rogers.

title: Baby Face
description: A young woman uses her sexual power to climb the corporate ladder in New York City, ruthlessly exploiting men to get ahead.

title: The Bitter Tea of General Yen
description: An American missionary in Shanghai is caught in the middle of the Chinese Civil War and falls under the protection of a powerful warlord.

title: Lady for a Day
description: A gangster helps an old apple seller pose as a wealthy society woman to impress her visiting daughter and her fiancé.

title: Ecstasy
description: A young woman, neglected by her older husband, finds passion in the arms of a young engineer. Famous for its controversial scenes.

title: Bombshell
description: A movie star is tired of her studio publicist creating scandals for her and tries to escape to a normal life, but he won't let her go easily.

title: Mystery of the Wax Museum
description: A disfigured sculptor opens a new wax museum in New York, where the statues look frighteningly lifelike.

title: Island of Lost Souls
description: A shipwrecked traveler is trapped on an island with a mad scientist who performs gruesome experiments on animals to turn them into humans.

title: Man's Castle
description: A tough, independent man living in a shantytown takes in a homeless woman, leading to a romance that challenges his desire for freedom.

title: Employees' Entrance
description: A tyrannical department store manager manipulates and dominates his employees, including a young woman he hires.

title: State Fair
description: A farming family heads to the Iowa State Fair, where each member hopes to find success and romance.

title: The Kennel Murder Case
description: Detective Philo Vance investigates a murder where the victim seems to have been killed by someone who couldn't have left the room.

title: Torch Singer
description: A young mother gives up her illegitimate child for adoption, becomes a successful nightclub singer, and then searches for her lost daughter.

title: Hard to Handle
description: A fast-talking con artist organizes a marathon dance contest and gets involved in various schemes to make a quick buck.

title: Counsellor at Law
description: A successful lawyer who climbed his way up from poverty faces a crisis when his past threatens to destroy his career and marriage.

title: Tugboat Annie
description: The female captain of a tugboat tries to keep her drunken husband in line while ensuring their son grows up to be a success.

title: Gabriel Over the White House
description: A corrupt newly elected President of the United States suffers a car accident and wakes up as a divinely inspired dictator who solves the nation's problems.

title: The Eagle and the Hawk
description: Three WWI pilots in France deal with the horrors of war in different ways, leading to tragedy and conflict.

title: Only Yesterday
description: After the 1929 stock market crash, a woman reflects on her past love affair with a soldier during World War I.

title: The Prizefighter and the Lady
description: A sailor-turned-prizefighter falls for a gangster's moll, threatening his career and his life.

title: Christopher Strong
description: A female aviator falls in love with a married aristocrat, leading to an illicit affair with tragic consequences.

title: Dancing Lady
description: A burlesque dancer gets her big break on Broadway thanks to a rich playboy, but she falls for the show's demanding stage manager.

title: Midnight Mary
description: A woman on trial for murder recounts her hard life, from poverty to involvement with gangsters.

title: Penthouse
description: A lawyer defends a racketeer accused of murder, but when the lawyer is framed for another murder, he must find the real killer.

title: Picture Snatcher
description: An ex-con decides to go straight and becomes a photographer for a trashy tabloid newspaper, using his street smarts to get sensational photos.

title: Roman Scandals
description: A kind-hearted delivery boy is knocked unconscious and dreams he is in ancient Rome, where he uncovers corruption.

title: Going Hollywood
description: A young woman follows a crooner to Hollywood and tries to win his heart and a part in his new movie.

title: The Mayor of Hell
description: A racketeer takes over a reform school and tries to improve conditions for the boys, but faces opposition from corrupt officials.

title: Hold Your Man
description: A con artist and a small-time crook fall in love, but their pasts threaten to tear them apart.

title: The Bowery
description: A saloon keeper and a rival gang leader compete for control of the Bowery in 1890s New York.

title: Female
description: A tough female executive runs an auto factory and treats her male employees like playthings, until she meets an independent designer.

title: International House
description: Various eccentrics gather at a hotel in China to bid on a new invention, the 'radioscope'.
